# Sprint 3 Report

**Sprint Duration:** 11/12-11/19  
**Team:** Daniel Lee, Nick Loxton, Lucia Patino, William Sharpe

---

## Sprint Goal & Achievement

**Sprint Goal:** Complete user authentication system and enable users to manually create, save, and manage recipes with ingredients, instructions, and optional images.

**Achievement Status:** ✅ **GOAL ACHIEVED**

All 6 committed user stories (29 story points) completed with 100% completion rate. User authentication is fully functional, recipe creation with dynamic ingredients/instructions works seamlessly, image uploads are supported, and comprehensive unit tests ensure code quality.

**Key Success Factors:** Effective use of Django's authentication framework, well-planned database model design, comprehensive unit test coverage (10 tests, 100% pass rate), and clean code organization.

---

## User Journey Demo

**1. Registration → Login → Recipe Creation:**
User creates account → automatically logged in → clicks "Create Recipe" → fills form with title, description, ingredients (dynamic add/remove), instructions (numbered steps), and optional image → recipe saved to database → redirected to detail page.

**2. Recipe Management:**
Logged-in user clicks "My Recipes" → sees grid of all recipes → clicks recipe card → views full details (ingredients, instructions, image) → can navigate back to list or homepage.

**3. Logout:**
User clicks "Log out" → session terminated → redirected to homepage with login/register options.

**Demo Highlights:** All flows functional and intuitive, clear error handling, dynamic form fields enhance UX, images display correctly, seamless navigation.

