## Technical Progress

### What's Working Well
- **Authentication:** Django's built-in framework provides secure, reliable user management with seamless session handling
- **Data Model:** Well-structured models (Recipe, Ingredient, Step) with proper relationships, ImageField support, scalable design
- **Dynamic Forms:** JavaScript-powered ingredient/instruction fields with add/remove functionality, form validation
- **Code Quality:** 10 unit tests (100% pass), clean Django best practices, proper separation of concerns
- **Media Handling:** Image uploads working (file/URL), proper configuration, correct display

### Technical Challenges Remaining
1. **Image Storage:** Need cloud storage (S3/R2) for production (currently local)
2. **Code Review:** Need formal review process before PR merges
3. **User Testing:** Limited feedback during development; need early testing process
4. **Documentation:** Sprint 2 docs incomplete; need historical data
5. **Recipe CRUD:** Missing edit/delete functionality; prioritize for Sprint 4

---

## Sprint Retrospective Highlights

### Key Insights
**What Went Well:** (1) Successful authentication implementation, (2) Dynamic form UX, (3) Comprehensive test coverage, (4) Clean code organization, (5) Scalable database design

**What Didn't Go Well:** (1) Image upload config took more time than anticipated, (2) Sprint 2 documentation incomplete, (3) Limited user feedback during development

**What to Improve:** (1) Sprint planning & documentation (complete Sprint 2 review, establish template, include dependencies), (2) Development workflow (code reviews, weekly syncs, technical decision log), (3) User testing (create plan, identify test users, mid-sprint demos)

### Top Action Items
| Action | Owner | Deadline |
|--------|-------|----------|
| Complete Sprint 2 review | [Team Lead] | End Sprint 3 |
| Implement code review process | [Tech Lead] | Before Sprint 4 |
| Create user testing plan | [Product Owner] | Sprint 4 planning |
| Document technical dependencies | [Tech Lead] | End Sprint 3 |

---

## Sprint 4 Preview

**Priority Features:**
1. **Recipe Editing & Deletion** (High) - Edit existing recipes, delete with confirmation
2. **Recipe Search & Filtering** (High) - Search user's recipes, filter by tags/cuisine/dietary
3. **Enhanced UX** (Medium) - Password reset, email verification, improved error messages
4. **Social Features** (Medium) - Recipe sharing, favorites, comments, ratings

**Technical Improvements:** Migrate to cloud image storage, implement code review process, enhance test coverage, improve documentation

**Process Improvements:** Establish user testing workflow, improve sprint planning docs, enhance team communication

